壷@0e400d7af8f923cb1cb295f0d7f447d3795b7d52ae5e32febf15ef365c103e3eﾚTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #293'
Path: Highlights
Content:
Thanks to @LoicRiegel for two improvements to 
``into datetime``
 this week - The command can now use a timezone flag when parsing a specific format, and it also accepts 
``float``
s as input.
A few additional improvements come to 
``into datetime``
 with the upgrade of the 
``human-date-parser``
 crate. While we don't always remember to call out upstream improvements, Nushell

just wouldn't be possible without the contributions of numerous contributors outside and upstream from our repos. A huge thanks to these (usually) unsung heroes.
@pyz4 improved the 
``polars cast``
 command to accept a decimal precision and scale. Thank you!
@blindFS has enabled tab-complete for the built-in modules 
``std``
, 
``std-rfc``
, and their submodules. Woot! Thanks!
And thanks to @vansh284 for additional exact-match improvements for completions!
Finally, @mztikk added support on Windows for running scripts on the path.
As always, thank you to all the contributors this week!
壷@c6c1889491e4bf0eed69a5418be5e35d1eece3704905f0e47afae8165f773d4eﾚ	rTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #293'
Path: Features & Fixes
Content:
mztikk 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15486] considered PATH when running a command is a nushell script in Windows
.
fdncred:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15483] bumped to the latest Rust version
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15426] updated human-date-parser to 3.0
.
blindFS:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15471] refactored commands to be identified by name instead of span content
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15270] added stdlib virtual path completion & exportable completion
.
pyz4 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15464] ``polars cast``
: added a decimal option for the 
``dtype``
 parameter
.
WindSoilder:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15463] updated rand and rand_chacha to 0.9
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15462] updated shadow-rs to version 1
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15456] removed 
``-s``
 and 
``-p``
 options in 
``do``
.
migraine-user 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15461] fixed a typo in doc_config.nu and improved the description
.
ysthakur:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15458] enabled exact match behavior for any path with slashes
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15457] reverted "Improve completions for exact matches (Issue #14794)"
.
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15454] fixed upgrading and checking of typos
.
132ikl 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15442] added boolean examples to 
``any``
 and 
``all``
.
vansh284 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15387] improved completions for exact matches (Issue #14794)
.
LoicRiegel:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15370] fixed 
``into datetime``
 ignoring timezone with format
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15297] made 
``into duration``
 accept floats
.
